COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 656, L.D. 1648
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment provides that the Maine Arts Commission, the Maine State Museum
33 Commission and the Maine Historic Preservation Commission must accept private gifts,
44 grants and donations from individuals and organizations to fund the costs of replacing the
55 statues of Hannibal Hamlin and William King in the National Statuary Hall Collection and
66 to transport and display those statues in public view within the State House or on the
77 grounds of the State House.
88 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
99 (See attached)
